race.comment: MAURITA (12) appreciated the step up in distance last time out, recording a dogged win over 1990m at this track. Has been out to today's distance twice and filled a minor placing on both occasions. Worth following now that she is back in form. VERMEER (2) was in the money for the fourth time in five runs when runner-up over this distance at Grafton recently. Has only won two races, but both came here at today's journey. Well placed to grab an overdue victory. WHATJEUDOIN' (6) missed the frame for the first time in a while when midfield at Doomben last start. In a more suitable race today and can return to form. FLYING ROTHE (11) has found form, albeit on the Gold Coast poly. In the mix if it converts to turf. HAMILTON BROWN (8) has been a bit plain of late but gets to this trip for the first time which might be what he needs.
